   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Depending on the system configuration and
terminal placement, the cabinets can have top and/or bottom mounted
gland plates.</p>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">All the gland plates in the
system must be connected to the earth busbars.</note>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Connect Top Mounted Gland Plates</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that top earth busbar <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> is connected to the
protective earth through the gland plate.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Attach the top earth cables <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(H)</b> to the top earth busbar <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> with the fastening set <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b>. Tighten to 16 Nm (11.8
lb-ft).</p>
                  <note conref="Connecting_the_Earth_Busbar_CPT_0000425822.dita#ConnectingTheEarthBusbar-D20A7411/busbar_fastening_set"
                        class="- topic/note "/>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Attach the top earth cables <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(H)</b> to each gland plate
with the fastening sets <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(I)</b>. Tighten to 10 Nm (7.38 lb-ft).</p>
                  <note id="DependingOnTheConfigurationThereCan-E7A725EA" class="- topic/note ">Depending
on the configuration there can be either one or two gland plates.</note>
               </li>
            </ol>
